<title type="html"><![CDATA[DumbNES]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=438&amp;p=3119#p3119"><![CDATA[
Sounds interesting.  So "DumbNES" is a CopyNES &amp; Flash Cart?  In other words, it is probably the first NES copier!  Why don't you make an account for these forums and log in?  That way we can all know which hardware project this is exactly.  There are multiple projects at different stages of completion.  MidiNES, CopyNES, FPGA NES, Squeedo, and others.  However, no other project seems to have goals of a full featured copier, as your DumbNES does.<br /><br />The bare minimum to be considered a console copier, in my opinion, is to be able to backup most of the console's game and to be able to play these backups, without the original cart, on the actual system.  CopyNES with a RAM cart can't do this, as it can backup any game, but it can't play any backup.  FPGA NES can't backup games and it can't play them on a real NES.  Squeedo is more akin to Color Dream's Super Cart, i.e. a cart with a powerful mapper.  MidiNES is a NES cart for doing professional audio stuff.<br /><br />So most of these projects are distinct in their feature set, except for CopyNES which appears to be subsumed, feature-wise, by DumbNES.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=94">Jagasian</a> — Tue Jul 26, 2005 12:44 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
